cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on improving the energy-efficiency and performance of continuous vision tasks using algorithm-architecture co-design. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of an Image Signal Processor (ISP) and System-on-a-Chip (SoC) architecture, which are related to the areas of augmented reality (cs.AR), embedded systems (cs.EM), and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also mentions measurement and synthesis results, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
